Fix initial migration with non-default settings

Migration 0002 set a couple of foreign key to settings.AUTH_USER_MODEL
then migration 0003 try to remove one of these field. If this migration
is played with STRIPE_USER_MODEL set to something different than
AUTH_USER_MODEL, this migration will fail due to a lacking dependency.

This commit add the missing dependency.

Fix non-initial migration with python 2.7

Prior to python 3, string literal were ascii string. These cause
exception if they contains raw unicode character and we pass them as
sole argument to the unicode function.

This exact scenario happen during non-initial migration with
StripeSubscriptionPlan.statement_descriptor and
StripeSubscriptionPlan.trial_period_days' help_text.

Importing unicode_literals from __future__ look like a nice solution to
this problem.
